@BTaskaya
I have added tests.
Travis build is in progress.

@micafer Thank you for your contribution!

Unfortunately the old path is no longer covered by tests. Are the OpenStack versions that need the old path still supported? If yes, we need somehow two tests to test the two paths. If it can be removed, then let's do that!

I don't have other issues with your code. Thanks!

It would be in libcloud/test/dns/test_powerdns.py in the `test_create_record` function, and it's possible that fixtures in libcloud/test/dns/fixtures/powerdns/ would have to change.

However I'm worried here that we're changing the behavior for all PowerDNS versions (3 and 4) while we would like to only change the behavior for PowerDNS 4.

@ktdreyer can you please help to review this pull request? I'm trying to help but never used the DNS parts of libcloud. Thanks!

@tintoy the `filter` method returns a list in Python 2 and an iterator in Python 3 (IList vs IEnumerable) and so cannot be indexed https://travis-ci.org/apache/libcloud/jobs/338753055#L979

Workarounds are: Don't use filter. Use a list comprehension
OR, convert to list around the filter response, e.g. list(filter(x))
